4 applicable to the taxing district;
5 (2) The amount allowed to be imposed without an excess tax levy;
6 (3) The date, time, and location of the public hearing at which the governing body will
7 vote to impose an excess tax levy;
8 (4) The estimated increase in property taxes in the district, per one hundred thousand
9 dollars of taxable value, as a result of the excess tax levy; and
10 (5) The intended use of moneys collected from the excess tax levy being considered.
11 The governing body of the district shall, at the public hearing, provide taxpayers
12 with an opportunity to comment on the excess tax levy.
